What is the correct JavaScript syntax to change the content of the HTML element <p id="demo">This is a demonstration.</p>?

 1 document.getElementById("p").innerHTML = "Hello World!";
>2 document.getElementById("demo").innerHTML = "Hello World!";
 3 #demo.innerHTML = "Hello World!";

Inside which HTML element do we put the JavaScript?

 1 <js>
>2 <script>
 3 <javascript>

Where is the correct place to insert a JavaScript?

>1 Both the <head> section and the <body> section are correct
 2 The <head> section
 3 The <body> section

What is the correct syntax for referring to an external script called "xxx.js"?

 1 <script name="xxx.js">
 2 <script href="xxx.js">
>3 <script src="xxx.js">

How can you add a comment in a JavaScript?

>1 //This is a comment
 2 'This is a comment
 3 <!--This is a comment-->


